    "assignee": "claude",
    "output": "Implemented the Excalidraw injection/extraction plan from task 3f410b5d.\n\n## Changes\n\n### src/pages/Draw.tsx\n- Added `excalidrawAPI` ref via `useState` for imperative API access\n- Added `initialData` loading from backend on mount (fetches from `/api/drawings/default`)\n- Added debounced `onChange` handler (2s) that auto-saves using `serializeAsJSON`\n- Shows loading state while fetching initial data\n- Uses proper Excalidraw types (`ExcalidrawImperativeAPI`, `AppState`, `BinaryFiles`, `ExcalidrawElement`)\n\n### server/index.ts\n- Added `DRAWINGS_DIR` config (auto-detects dev vs prod data directory)\n- `GET /api/drawings` — list all saved drawings\n- `GET /api/drawings/:id` — load a drawing by ID\n- `POST /api/drawings/:id` — save a drawing (stores as `.excalidraw` JSON file)\n- Broadcasts `drawing:updated` SSE events on save\n- Atomic writes via tmp file + rename (same pattern as tasks)\n\n### data/drawings/ and data-dev/drawings/\n- Created directories for drawing storage\n\n## How to verify\n1. Open /draw — canvas loads (shows 'Loading...' briefly, then Excalidraw)\n2. Draw something, wait 2s — check that `data/drawings/default.excalidraw` is created\n3. Refresh page — drawing persists\n4. `curl localhost:3001/api/drawings/default` — returns the saved JSON\n\n## Type check\n`npx tsc --noEmit` passes clean."
